<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8' standalone='no'?>
<!DOCTYPE issue SYSTEM "lwg-issue.dtd">

<issue num="4589" status="New">
<title><code>std::format</code> should escape null as <code>\0</code></title>
<section><sref ref="[format.string.escaped]"/></section>
<submitter>Tomasz Kamiński</submitter>
<date>10 Jun 2026</date>
<priority>99</priority>

<discussion>
<p>
As current specified the debug output of the <tt>std::format</tt> for the
string containing null terminator should escape it as <tt>\u{0}</tt> instead
of more conventional <tt>\0</tt>.
</p>

<pre>
std::string_view sv("a\0b", 3);
std::print("{:?}", sv); // "a\u{0}b" not "a\0b"
</pre>
</discussion>

<resolution>
<p>
This wording is relative to <paper num="N5046"/>.
</p>

<ol>
<li><p>Modify <sref ref="[tab:format.escape.sequences]"/>, Table 114 &mdash; Mapping of characters to escape sequences:</p>

<blockquote>
<table border="1">
<thead style="text-align: center">
<tr><th>Character</th><th>Escape sequence</th></tr>
</thead>
<tbody style="vertical-align: top">
<tr>
<td><ins>U+0000 NULL</ins></td>
<td><ins>\0</ins></td>
</tr>
<tr><td>&hellip;</td><td>&hellip;</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</blockquote>
</li>
</ol>

</resolution>

</issue>
